news.title: Soaring home prices push up average US homeowner equity growth
news.para: Homes with a mortgage gained an average of $51,500 in equity in the second quarter, an increase of 29.3% from the April-June quarter last year, according to real estate information company CoreLogic.

news.title: Australian house prices keep climbing, attract watchdog's eye
news.para: Stay-at-home orders did nothing to stop Sydney prices jumping 1.9% in the month and 23.6% for the year. Melbourne was up 15% on a year ago, Brisbane 20% and Perth 18%.

news.title: Gurugram civic body receives Rs 35.55 crore as property tax in September
news.para: The benefit of rebate and interest waiver was given to the property owners of Gurugram by the Haryana government till September 30. MCG officials said an amount of Rs 25.79 crore has been deposited from zone-3 and zone-4 areas.

news.title: Panchsheel Group gets Rs 249 crore from centre's stress fund to complete project
news.para: Panchsheel Greens II is the second project in Greater Noida which has got financial assistance from the stress fund. Earlier, Rs 165 crore was sanctioned to the Capital Athena project, Greater Noida Industrial Development Authority (GNIDA) said.

news.title: China new-home price growth at slowest in 18 months: Survey
news.para: New-home prices in 100 cities rose 0.14% in September from a month earlier, down from 0.2% growth in August, according to data from China Index Academy, one of the country's largest independent real estate research firms.

news.title: Piramal Capital & Housing Finance acquires DHFL via reverse merger
news.para: PCHFL has merged into DHFL with effect from September 30, 2021 pursuant to the reverse merger as contemplated under scheme of arrangement provided under the resolution plan, the company said in the regulatory filing.

news.title: Ashiana Housing buys 15.64 acres land in Chennai from Mahindra Lifespaces
news.para: In a regulatory filing, Ashiana Housing said the company has acquired a piece of land measuring 15.64 acres on perpetual lease basis from Mahindra Lifespaces within the township of Mahindra World City at Chennai (Tamil Nadu).

news.title: In a first, BMC to auction two seized choppers over property tax dues
news.para: Civic officials said the BMC had seized two helicopters from a company which had not paid property tax to the tune of Rs 4.1 crore.

news.title: OYO seeks Sebi nod for Rs 8,430-crore IPO
news.para: The firm incurred a loss of Rs 2,364.53 crore in FY19, which widened to Rs 13,122.77 crore in the following year but reduced to Rs 3,943.84 crore in FY21. It had aggregate outstanding borrowings of Rs 4,890.55 crore as of July 31, a part of which will be repaid from proceeds of the issue.

news.title: Construction of aqua line extension to Greater Noida west may begin this year
news.para: Officials in the Noida Metro Rail Corporation (NMRC) are expecting the Centre’s approval by the end of November. That will pave the way for construction to begin in December.

news.title: Kolkata civic body to implement eviction policy for dilapidated buildings
news.para: According to a civic official, the section 411 (4) of the building rules gives an executive or an assistant engineer of the KMC building department the right to demolish the parts of a building listed as “dangerous” that may endanger the lives of its occupants or inmates of the adjacent buildings.

news.title: Bihar: Sand mining to resume in eight districts from today
news.para: Sources said the mining in the remaining eight districts would be resumed after getting clearance from the state cabinet. The auction of authorised mining ghats will be done after the cabinet’s nod.

news.title: Delhi: 23 construction, demolition sites found violating dust control norms, says DPCC
news.para: The DPCC deployed 11 teams to carry out inspections in Connaught Place, Connaught Circus, Janpath, Munirka, R K Puram, Mahipalpur, Rangpuri, Mayapuri, Naraina Vihar, Vasant Kunj, Vasant Vihar, Nangal Raya, Sagarpur, Khan Market, Pandara Road, and areas surrounding ITO.

news.title: Punjab & Haryana HC reserves order in case of floor-wise sale of properties
news.para: The UT administration had submitted before the HC that no NOC was issued mentioning floor of property. On the HC directions, the UT had submitted an affidavit of assistant estate officer (AEO) Harjeet Singh Sandhu.

news.title: Greater Noida authority extends rebate offer on registry penalty of 2010 built-up scheme
news.para: "There are about 3,300 such allottees who have not yet registered their properties. Due to this, more than Rs 200 crore of the Greater Noida Authority is stuck as premium and lease rent," the authority said in a statement.
